# Slidev Frontmatter Configuration Guide

## Required Frontmatter
When creating a presentation in [slides.md](mdc:slides.md), include these essential frontmatter configurations from [temp/slides2.md](mdc:temp/slides2.md):

```yaml
---
theme: seriph
background: /image/slides/image.png
title: Your Presentation Title
info: |
  ## Slidev Starter Template
  Presentation slides for developers.
class: text-center
drawings:
  persist: false
transition: slide-left
mdc: true
highlighter: shiki
lineNumbers: false
---
```

## Key Configuration Elements
- `theme`: Use 'seriph' theme for consistent styling
- `background`: Set slide background image (stored in /image/slides/)
- `title`: Update with your specific presentation title
- `class`: Maintain text-center for title slide
- `transition`: Keep slide-left for smooth transitions
- `mdc`: Enable Markdown Components syntax

## Remember
This frontmatter should be at the top of [slides.md](mdc:slides.md) with proper configuration for your specific presentation topic.
